t, more than 23,000 people were diagnosed with dengue, compared to 43,854 cases during all of July.\n\nMore than 100 people have died so far this month, over a third as many deaths from the illness during all of last year.\n\nIn 2022, 62,382 people were infected and 281 people died of dengue, according to government figures.\n\nDengue causes flu-like symptoms that most people recover from, but also can rapidly lead to internal bleeding, organ failure and even death.\n\nThere generally is no specific treatment for the disease, but vaccines are available. Other countries, such as Cyprus and Bolivia, also have seen outbreaks this year.\n\n(VOA/AP)","title":"Dengue outbreak in Bangladesh sparks alarm after 364 people die this year","url":"http://english.khabarhub.com/2023/12/314213/","video":[]}
